            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 10,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "PURPOSE"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 11,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The purpose of this Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) is to:"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 12,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Outline key pathway touch points for consultants"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 13,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Document process for managing referral triage"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 14,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Provide a baseline for future process improvements"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 15,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Assist in developing baseline for the development of training material"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 16,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "OVERVIEW"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 17,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 18.0,
                "text": "The consultant body are responsible for the triage of the majority of elective pathway referrals (18 week clock starts) and therefore must understand the  week clock codes and how Lorenzo manages them during various patient activity points."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 18,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "With the introduction of an electronic patient record in 2017 the organisation took the opportunity to digitise paper referrals received from GPs and other organisations and manage the triage process with an electronic \u2018in tray'"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 19,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Role \u2013 Consultant and members of referral triage teams Procedure \u2013 Referral triage"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Additional guidance"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "This SOP does not include the guide to using e-RS. It is assumed that clinicians running services published to e-RS are aware of the steps required to cancel/accept referrals via this system. It is also assumed that users understand the implication to NOT performing these actions in e-RS; namely inappropriate referrals or appointments within the wrong clinic. Guidance can be sought directly from NHS Digital website: https://digital.nhs.uk/services/e-referral-service/providers/service-provides-of-directly-bookable- services-dbs"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 22,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "As GP referrals are being managed via e-RS the only referrals that will come manually into Lorenzo are the following:"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 23,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Con2Con (existing condition)"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 24,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Tertiary providers"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 25,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Opticians / dentists"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 26,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Other acute trusts"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 27,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "E-RS ASIs (these are referrals that come via e-RS but due to capacity cannot be booked and are found on the \u2018appointment slot issue' list). This is a manual process managed by the service booking teams."
            }
        },
